{"synckey":1679375838,"updated":[{"bookId":"3300051655","bookmarkId":"3300051655_4_1914-1965","createTime":1679375838,"chapterUid":4,"colorStyle":2,"type":1,"markText":"邓普顿、蒂施、内夫和沃伦·巴菲特这些人与普通投资者的区别在于，他们具有坚韧的内心和对于创造财富的自信。","range":"1914-1965"},{"bookId":"3300051655","bookmarkId":"3300051655_4_484-580","createTime":1679169858,"chapterUid":4,"colorStyle":2,"type":1,"markText":"分析师兼作家马丁·弗里德森(Martin Fridson)指出：“从来没有一个群体会同时出现在《福布斯》400强榜上，原因很简单，当一个人的做法和周围人一样时，他显然就无法从竞争中脱颖而出。”","range":"484-580"},{"bookId":"3300051655","bookmarkId":"3300051655_3_1472-1618","createTime":1679169730,"chapterUid":3,"colorStyle":1,"type":1,"markText":"从20世纪50年代起，他所做的就是募集资金的工作。他在金融行业里寻找廉价的资本，通常是收购一家能够产生现金流的公司，然后把这些现金流投资到年化收益20%～30%的项目中去。在这个过程中，每增加一美元投资都能等值转化为上市公司伯克希尔·哈撒韦(Berkshire Hathaway)的内在价值。","range":"1472-1618"}],"removed":[],"chapters":[{"title":"亿万富翁的特质","chapterUid":4,"chapterIdx":4},{"title":"第一部分 巴菲特财富之路","chapterUid":3,"chapterIdx":3}],"book":{"bookId":"3300051655","version":266832236,"format":"epub","soldout":1,"bookStatus":1,"cover":"https://cdn.weread.qq.com/weread/cover/20/cpplatform_7sm1c2dd54bnqfefrdhqhr/s_cpplatform_7sm1c2dd54bnqfefrdhqhr1678356366.jpg","title":"巴菲特教你选择成长股","author":"蒂默西·韦克","coverBoxInfo":{"blurhash":"KfI}*T4:E3~WRPNG4n%1t6","colors":[{"key":"1/4","hex":"#121b35"},{"key":"1/6","hex":"#081a41"},{"key":"1/8","hex":"#00184c"},{"key":"2/4","hex":"#26304b"},{"key":"2/6","hex":"#1e2f58"},{"key":"2/8","hex":"#112e65"},{"key":"3/4","hex":"#3c4765"},{"key":"3/6","hex":"#344672"},{"key":"3/8","hex":"#2a467e"},{"key":"3/12","hex":"#004398"},{"key":"4/6","hex":"#4e5f89"},{"key":"4/10","hex":"#3a5ea3"},{"key":"4/4","hex":"#565f7c"},{"key":"5/10","hex":"#5578bd"},{"key":"5/4","hex":"#6f7994"},{"key":"5/8","hex":"#5f79b0"},{"key":"6/4","hex":"#8993ad"},{"key":"6/6","hex":"#8193bc"},{"key":"6/8","hex":"#7993ca"},{"key":"6/12","hex":"#6292e8"},{"key":"7/8","hex":"#91aee6"},{"key":"7/10","hex":"#87adf7"},{"key":"7/12","hex":"#78adff"},{"key":"8/4","hex":"#bcc8e2"},{"key":"8/6",